"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"<植物的熱敏感物質-1>\\n植物在烹調的過程中，會因加熱高溫煮熟，殺滅對人體有害的細菌，維持人體的健康。\\n但也有許多文章探討加熱的過程，會使植物的營養流失一部份。\\n這些因為溫度的提高而流失的營養成份，是否就能視為植物所含有的熱敏感物質呢？\\n\\n首先，植物的水溶性營養素，如維他命c，會隨著水煮的過程而溶於水。\\n\\n抗氧化的營養素則會因為高溫而流失。\\n\\n脂溶性的營養素，則需和油一起料理，才能增加脂溶性營養素的吸收。\\n\\n如此概觀而論，抗氧化的營養素，對植物而言，會隨接觸環境的溫度改變，產生明顯的影響，可以確定，抗氧化的成份便是植物的熱敏感物質。\\n\\n以後再針對抗氧化營養素做更多的討論。\\n\\n<Plant's Heat Sensitive Substance-1>\\nIn the process of cooking, plants will be cooked at high temperature due to heating, killing bacteria that are harmful to the human body and maintaining the health of the human body.\\nHowever, there are also many articles discussing the process of heating, which will cause a part of the nutrient loss of plants.\\nCan these nutrients lost due to the increase in temperature be regarded as heat-sensitive substances contained in plants?\\n\\nFirst, the water-soluble nutrients of plants, such as vitamin C, will dissolve in water during the boiling process.\\n\\nAntioxidant nutrients will be lost due to high temperature.\\n\\nFat-soluble nutrients need to be cooked together with oil to increase the absorption of fat-soluble nutrients.\\n\\nIn this overview, antioxidant nutrients, for plants, will change with the temperature of the environment, and have a significant impact. It can be determined that the antioxidant components are the heat-sensitive substances of the plant.\\n\\nThere will be more discussions on antioxidant nutrients in the future.\",\"timestamp\":1640916548,\"title\":\"<植物的熱敏感物質-1>Plant's Heat Sensitive Substance-1\"},\"digest\":\"eWAQIMZ4_DgU6mjTYwrCjOr-e47Rb49gEdTHkHKa1U0\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xef9d81473Ea7E87cFc707346B204Cb31cCEEDB1B\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"u-3KuTkoDDIwvDuFVKjR3Qff_xtuoBy2U9ObtcqcqCc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"hZ01KzGe-MCVXVtPdNPIZbbkegUqv6mxu5uP_BHFWEU\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"35wSgN9lX1ZWUmqpGVkUcDhhK7wUpFafQwPgLKBV5x25GgpXygRY3Ni4-jKDc5dxAIeX